original: Lindahl, Sven Johan, civilingenjör, stadsingenjör, stadsarkitekt, Falkenberg, f. 5/7/03 i Malmö av gross-handl. Ernst L. o. Ulrika Carolina Nilsson. G. 30 m. Stina Hedberg. Barn: Maud f. 34, Monica 38. — Stud:ex. i Malmö 22, CTI (V) 23-27. Vägkontr. v. Bara härads vägstyr. 27-28, anst. v. Malmö hamnförvaltn. 28-31, h. Sthlms slussbyggn :komm. 31-35, stadsing. i Falkenberg 35-38, byggn:-chef i A-B Turitz & Co. 38-41, i A-B Ferd. Lundquist & Co. i Gbg 41-46, num. stadsing. o. stadsarkit. i Falkenberg. Arkit. f. Hotell Strandbaden o. folkrestaurang i Falkenberg samt f. div. industribyggn., inredn :arkit. f. hotell o. restauranger i Sv:e. Led. av Tekn. samf. i Gbg, SVR o. Sv. tekn:-fören. Hobbies : golf o. musik. Första pris tills. m. civ :ing. Erik Garberg i internat. hamnplantävl. i Abo 30.
translated: Lindahl, Sven Johan, civil engineer, city engineer, city architect, Falkenberg, b. 5/7/03 in Malmö to merchant Ernst L. and Ulrika Carolina Nilsson. Married on 30, to Stina Hedberg. Children: Maud b. 34, Monica b. 38. — Completed high school in Malmö in 22, CTI (V) 23-27. Road contractor for Bara district road authority from 27-28, employed by Malmö port administration from 28-31, commissioned by Stockholm lock building committee from 31-35, city engineer in Falkenberg from 35-38, construction manager at A-B Turitz & Co. from 38-41, at A-B Ferd. Lundquist & Co. in Gothenburg from 41-46, appointed city engineer and city architect in Falkenberg. Architect for Hotel Strandbaden and public restaurant in Falkenberg, as well as various industrial buildings, interior architect for hotels and restaurants in Sweden. Member of the Technical Society in Gothenburg, SVR, and Swedish Technical Association. Hobbies: golf and music. First prize together with civil engineer Erik Garberg in international harbor planning competition in Turku in 30.
